<!doctype html>
<html class="js full-height" lang="{{ request.locale.iso_code }}" dir="{{ request.locale.direction | default: 'ltr' }}">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
    {%- comment -%}
      theme-color — pulls the default color-scheme surface colour so
      Chrome/Safari paint the address-bar and PWA chrome in the brand
      background instead of defaulting to browser chrome. Falls back
      to the Kitchero brand ivory when the scheme is not yet saved.
      Mirrors the logic in layout/theme.liquid so coming-soon visitors
      get the same branded browser chrome as the live storefront.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- liquid
      assign default_scheme = settings.kt_schemes | default: settings.color_schemes
      assign theme_color = '#FAFAF9'
      if default_scheme and default_scheme['scheme-1'] and default_scheme['scheme-1'].settings.surface
        assign theme_color = default_scheme['scheme-1'].settings.surface
      endif
    -%}
    <meta name="theme-color" content="{{ theme_color }}">
    <link rel="canonical" href="{{ canonical_url }}">

    {%- comment -%}
      cdn.shopify.com hosts password-page images (logo, background). Pre-
      connecting here saves the DNS + TLS round-trip (~150–300 ms on
      mobile) before the HTML parser discovers the <img>. crossorigin
      is required because Shopify serves image assets as CORS-enabled
      responses.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://cdn.shopify.com" crossorigin>

    {%- unless settings.kt_heading_font.system? and settings.kt_body_font.system? -%}
      <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.shopifycdn.com" crossorigin>
    {%- endunless -%}

    {%- comment -%}
      hreflang alternates — one <link> per published locale so search
      engines serve the right translation per user locale. Emitted only
      when the shop has more than one published locale; x-default falls
      back to the primary locale. Password page is crawlable during
      store-setup and pre-launch periods, so SEO signals still matter.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- if shop.published_locales.size > 1 -%}
      {%- for locale in shop.published_locales -%}
        {%- if locale.primary -%}
          <link rel="alternate" hreflang="{{ locale.iso_code }}" href="{{ request.origin }}{{ request.path }}">
        {%- else -%}
          <link rel="alternate" hreflang="{{ locale.iso_code }}" href="{{ request.origin }}/{{ locale.iso_code }}{{ request.path }}">
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- endfor -%}
      <link rel="alternate" hreflang="x-default" href="{{ request.origin }}{{ request.path }}">
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- if settings.kt_favicon != blank -%}
      <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="{{ settings.kt_favicon | image_url: width: 32, height: 32 }}">
      <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="192x192" href="{{ settings.kt_favicon | image_url: width: 192, height: 192 }}">
      <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="{{ settings.kt_favicon | image_url: width: 180, height: 180 }}">
    {%- endif -%}

    <title>{{ page_title | default: shop.name }}</title>

    {% if page_description %}
      <meta name="description" content="{{ page_description | escape }}">
    {% endif %}

    {% render 'meta-tags' %}

    {{ content_for_header }}

    {%- comment -%}
      Render the shared kt-* CSS custom properties (colors, spacing,
      shadows) via the shared kt-css-variables snippet. This snippet
      itself emits @font-face declarations (body regular/bold/italic/
      bold-italic + heading) AND the per-scheme design tokens AND the
      global tokens — so the inline `{% style %}` block that used to
      live here was redundant and actually double-defined every
      font-face (CSSOM parses both, wastes ~1-2KB inline bytes).

      theme.liquid renders this before base.css; password.liquid
      needed the same plumbing so the customer-forms + account CSS
      loaded on /password don't resolve `var(--kt-stone-900)` etc.
      to their CSS initial values.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- render 'kt-css-variables' -%}

    {{ 'base.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

    {%- comment -%}
      Font preloads — password page has minimal content but the logo
      and coming-soon heading are the LCP on most visits. Preloading
      the body + heading WOFF2 files lets the browser start the font
      download in parallel with the CSS, cutting FOUT/CLS during the
      brief pre-launch window. Gated on non-system fonts because
      Shopify's font_url returns blank for system font stacks.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- unless settings.kt_body_font.system? -%}
      {% comment %}theme-check-disable AssetPreload{% endcomment %}
      <link rel="preload" as="font" href="{{ settings.kt_body_font | font_url }}" type="font/woff2" crossorigin>
      {% comment %}theme-check-enable AssetPreload{% endcomment %}
    {%- endunless -%}
    {%- unless settings.kt_heading_font.system? -%}
      {% comment %}theme-check-disable AssetPreload{% endcomment %}
      <link rel="preload" as="font" href="{{ settings.kt_heading_font | font_url }}" type="font/woff2" crossorigin>
      {% comment %}theme-check-enable AssetPreload{% endcomment %}
    {%- endunless -%}
  </head>

  <body class="password gradient">
    <a class="skip-to-content-link button visually-hidden" href="#MainContent">
      {{ 'kt.a11y.skip_to_text' | t }}
    </a>

    <main id="MainContent" class="password-main">
      {{ content_for_layout }}
    </main>

    <ul hidden>
      <li id="a11y-new-window-message">{{ 'kt.a11y.link.new_window' | t }}</li>
    </ul>
  </body>
</html>
